<p>
	Dave and John are back with a huge show this week, absolutely packed with questions, answers, tips, and cool stuff found. First it&#39;s helping Safari find its shadow, then solving some screensaver timing issues caused by Mountain Lion. John bought a new (cheap!) router that seems to work great, so he discusses that, too. Then it&#39;s some follow-ups to why your Mac&#39;s name might appear multiple times on your network, plus some advice for spreading your iTunes library around. And it wouldn&#39;t be the same if your geeks didn&#39;t answer a question about their own MGG App. All this and more, right here, for you, for free. Download today and enjoy!</p>
<p>
	Note: Shownotes are complete!</p>
